From: Sean Christopherson <seanjc@google.com>
Date: Fri, 1 May 2026 13:22:27 -0700
Subject: KVM: SEV: Ignore MMIO requests of length '0'
Patch-mainline: v7.1-rc6
Git-commit: 1aa8a6dc7dac8b83234b53518311bf78231f4fa5
References: git-fixes

Explicitly ignore MMIO requests of length '0', so that setting up the
software scratch area (and other code) doesn't have to worry about
underflowing the length, and to allow for special casing '0' in the
future.

Fixes: 8f423a80d299 ("KVM: SVM: Support MMIO for an SEV-ES guest")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Reviewed-by: Tom Lendacky <thomas.lendacky@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Sean Christopherson <seanjc@google.com>
Message-ID: <20260501202250.2115252-3-seanjc@google.com>
Signed-off-by: Paolo Bonzini <pbonzini@redhat.com>
Acked-by: Carlos López <clopez@suse.de>
---
 arch/x86/kvm/svm/sev.c |   24 ++++++++++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

--- a/arch/x86/kvm/svm/sev.c
+++ b/arch/x86/kvm/svm/sev.c
@@ -2922,26 +2922,38 @@ int sev_handle_vmgexit(struct kvm_vcpu *
 
 	exit_code = kvm_get_cached_sw_exit_code(control);
 	switch (exit_code) {
-	case SVM_VMGEXIT_MMIO_READ:
-		ret = setup_vmgexit_scratch(svm, true, control->exit_info_2);
+	case SVM_VMGEXIT_MMIO_READ: {
+		u64 len = control->exit_info_2;
+
+		if (!len)
+			return 1;
+
+		ret = setup_vmgexit_scratch(svm, true, len);
 		if (ret)
 			break;
 
 		ret = kvm_sev_es_mmio_read(vcpu,
 					   control->exit_info_1,
-					   control->exit_info_2,
+					   len,
 					   svm->sev_es.ghcb_sa);
 		break;
-	case SVM_VMGEXIT_MMIO_WRITE:
-		ret = setup_vmgexit_scratch(svm, false, control->exit_info_2);
+	}
+	case SVM_VMGEXIT_MMIO_WRITE: {
+		u64 len = control->exit_info_2;
+
+		if (!len)
+			return 1;
+
+		ret = setup_vmgexit_scratch(svm, false, len);
 		if (ret)
 			break;
 
 		ret = kvm_sev_es_mmio_write(vcpu,
 					    control->exit_info_1,
-					    control->exit_info_2,
+					    len,
 					    svm->sev_es.ghcb_sa);
 		break;
+	}
 	case SVM_VMGEXIT_NMI_COMPLETE:
 		++vcpu->stat.nmi_window_exits;
 		svm->nmi_masked = false;
